POSTGRES TABLESPACE CREATE:
---------------------------

STEPS:

1. Create the directory on the server:

	sudo mkdir /path/to/tablespace
	
	sudo chown postgres:postgres /path/to/tablespace
	
	sudo chmod 700 /path/to/tablespace
	
	
	
2. Create the tablespace in PostgreSQL:	

	sudo su postgres

	psql
	
	CREATE TABLESPACE tablespace_name OWNER username LOCATION '/path/to/tablespace';
	
	
	
2. create database if not exist:

	sudo su postgres
	
	psql
	
	create database database_name;
	
	\q
	
	
	
3. grant a user to the database:

	psql -d template1 -c "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE database_name to username;
	

		
3. Creating a Table in the Tablespace:

	psql -h hostname -U username -d database_name

	CREATE TABLE table_name (
	    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	    name TEXT
	) TABLESPACE tablespace_name;
	
4. Move Existing Tables to a Tablespace:


	ALTER TABLE table_name SET TABLESPACE tablespace_name;
	

